# 1945

1945 ([MCMXLV](/Roman_numerals)) was a [common year starting on Monday](/Common_year_starting_on_Monday) of the [Gregorian calendar](/Gregorian_calendar), the 1945th year of the [Common Era](/Common_Era) (CE) and [Anno Domini](/Anno_Domini) (AD) designations, the 945th year of the [2nd&#160;millennium](/2nd_millennium), the 45th year of the [20th&#160;century](/20th_century), and the 6th year of the [1940s](/1940s) decade.

## Calendar year

A turning point &#91;1&#93; in [human history](/Human_history), 1945 marked the end of [World War II](/World_War_II), concluding with the definitive defeat and subsequent occupation of [Nazi Germany](/Nazi_Germany) and the [Empire of Japan](/Empire_of_Japan). It also stands as the year in which the horrors of the [Nazi concentration camps](/Nazi_concentration_camps) were brought to light through liberation, and it remains the only year in history where [atomic weapons](/Atomic_weapon) have been deployed in actual warfare, specifically through the [atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki](/Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki).

### Events

[World War II](/World_War_II) will be abbreviated as "WWII" throughout this chronicle.

#### January

*   Main article: [January 1945](/January_1945)

*   **January 1**: WWII: [Germany](/Nazi_Germany) initiates [Operation Bodenplatte](/Operation_Bodenplatte), a last-ditch effort by the [Luftwaffe](/Luftwaffe) to cripple [Allied](/Allies_of_World_War_II) air forces stationed in the [Low Countries](/Low_Countries). &#91;2&#93; In the aftermath of this operation, the [Chenogne massacre](/Chenogne_massacre) allegedly occurred near the village of Chenogne, Belgium, where German prisoners of war were reportedly killed by American forces.
*   **January 1**: The [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union) agrees to enter the [Pacific War](/Pacific_War) against Japan once hostilities against Germany have concluded.
*   **January 2**: The British admiral [Sir Bertram Ramsay](/Bertram_Ramsay), instrumental in the Dunkirk evacuation, dies.
*   **January 3**: The American mystic [Edgar Cayce](/Edgar_Cayce), known for his psychic readings, passes away.
*   **January 4**: [Ricardo Jiménez Oreamuno](/Ricardo_Jim%C3%A9nez_Oreamuno), who served three terms as [President of Costa Rica](/President_of_Costa_Rica), dies.
*   **January 5**: [Josefa Llanes Escoda](/Josefa_Llanes_Escoda), a prominent Filipino women's [suffrage](/Suffrage) advocate and founder of the [Girl Scouts of the Philippines](/Girl_Scouts_of_the_Philippines), dies. [Edith Frank](/Edith_Frank), the mother of [Anne Frank](/Anne_Frank), also dies this month, succumbing to typhus in [Bergen-Belsen concentration camp](/Bergen-Belsen_concentration_camp).
*   **January 6**: WWII: The German offensive manages to recapture [Esztergom](/Esztergom) in [Hungary](/Kingdom_of_Hungary_(1920%E2%80%931946)) from Soviet forces.
*   **January 7**: The American sculptor [Alexander Stirling Calder](/Alexander_Stirling_Calder) dies. [Thomas McGuire](/Thomas_McGuire), an American fighter ace of World War II, is killed in action.
*   **January 9**: [Jüri Uluots](/J%C3%BCri_Uluots), the 8th [Prime Minister of Estonia](/Prime_Minister_of_Estonia), dies.
*   **January 10**: [Pēteris Juraševskis](/P%C4%93teris_Jura%C5%A1evskis), the 8th [Prime Minister of Latvia](/Prime_Minister_of_Latvia), dies.
*   **January 12**: [Teresio Olivelli](/Teresio_Olivelli), an Italian [Roman Catholic](/Roman_Catholic) soldier and venerable, dies.
*   **January 15**: [Pedro Abad Santos](/Pedro_Abad_Santos), a Filipino politician and brother of [José Abad Santos](/Jos%C3%A9_Abad_Santos), dies.
*   **January 16**: [José Fabella](/Jos%C3%A9_Fabella), a Filipino physician, dies.
*   **January 17**: [Walter Ulbricht](/Walter_Ulbricht) becomes the leader of the German [Communists](/Communism) in Moscow.
*   **January 18**: [The Holocaust](/The_Holocaust): The [SS](/SS) initiates the evacuation of [Auschwitz concentration camp](/Auschwitz_concentration_camp). Approximately 60,000 prisoners, predominantly Jewish, are forced on death marches to other locations in Germany, with an estimated 15,000 perishing. Those too ill to march are left behind without any provisions.
*   **January 19**: [The Holocaust](/The_Holocaust): Soviet forces liberate the [Łódź Ghetto](/%C5%81%C3%B3d%C5%BA_Ghetto). Of the original 164,000 inhabitants, only 877 Jews remain at this point. &#91;6&#93;
*   **January 20**: Germany commences the [Evacuation of East Prussia](/Evacuation_of_East_Prussia).
*   **January 21–22**: A devastating collision occurs at the [Grünhagen](/Zielonka_Pas%C5%82%C4%99cka) railroad station in [East Prussia](/East_Prussia) as two trains heading for [Elbing](/Elbl%C4%85g) derail. At dawn, the station is overrun by [Soviet Army](/Soviet_Army) infantry and tanks, resulting in the deaths of approximately 140 to 150 people.
*   **January 23**: WWII: Hungary formally agrees to an [armistice](/Armistice) with the [Allies](/Allies_of_World_War_II). German Grand Admiral [Karl Dönitz](/Karl_D%C3%B6nitz) orders the commencement of [Operation Hannibal](/Operation_Hannibal), a massive sea evacuation of German troops and civilians from the [Courland Pocket](/Courland_Pocket), [East Prussia](/Evacuation_of_East_Prussia), and the [Polish Corridor](/Polish_Corridor). This operation aims to rescue an estimated 800,000–900,000 German civilians and 350,000 soldiers from the advancing [Soviet forces](/Red_Army). The evacuation of Germans from [Grünhagen](/Zielonka_Pas%C5%82%C4%99cka) also takes place.
*   **January 24**: WWII: [AP](/Associated_Press) [war correspondent](/War_correspondent) [Joseph Morton](/Joseph_Morton_(correspondent)), alongside nine [OSS](/Office_of_Strategic_Services) men and four [SOE](/Special_Operations_Executive) agents, are executed by German forces at [Mauthausen concentration camp](/Mauthausen_concentration_camp). This execution is carried out under Hitler's [Commando Order](/Commando_Order) of 1942, which mandated the immediate execution of all captured Allied [commandos](/Commando) or [saboteurs](/Sabotage) without trial, even if they were in uniform. Morton is noted as the only [Allied](/Allies_of_World_War_II) correspondent to suffer this fate at the hands of the [Axis](/Axis_powers) during the war.
*   **January 25**: WWII: Hitler appoints [Heinrich Himmler](/Heinrich_Himmler) to command the newly formed [Army Group Vistula](/Army_Group_Vistula) (Heeresgruppe Weichsel), tasking him with halting the Soviet [Red Army](/Red_Army)'s [Vistula–Oder offensive](/Vistula%E2%80%93Oder_offensive) into [Pomerania](/Pomerania), despite Himmler's distinct lack of military experience. &#91;7&#93;
*   **January 26**: WWII: U.S. Army Staff Sergeant [Audie Murphy](/Audie_Murphy), aged 19, performs an act of valor near [Holtzwihr](/Holtzwihr), France, for which he is awarded the [Medal of Honor](/Medal_of_Honor).
*   **January 27**: [The Holocaust](/The_Holocaust): The Soviet [Red Army](/Red_Army) liberates the [Auschwitz](/Auschwitz_concentration_camp) and Birkenau concentration camps.
*   **January 30**: WWII:
    *   The MV [Wilhelm Gustloff](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MV_Wilhelm_Gustloff), carrying over 10,000 German civilians fleeing Gotenhafen ([Gdynia](/Gdynia)), is sunk in [Gdańsk Bay](/Gda%C5%84sk_Bay) by three [torpedoes](/Torpedo) fired from the Soviet submarine S-13 in the [Baltic Sea](/Baltic_Sea). An estimated 9,400 lives are lost, including 5,000 children, making it the single greatest loss of life in a maritime disaster in history.
    *   The [Raid at Cabanatuan](/Raid_at_Cabanatuan) is executed: 121 American soldiers and 800 Filipino guerrillas successfully liberate 813 American [prisoners of war](/Prisoners_of_war) from the Japanese-held camp in [Cabanatuan](/Cabanatuan), [Philippines](/Philippines).
    *   [Adolf Hitler](/Adolf_Hitler) delivers his final public address via broadcast radio, expressing his conviction that Germany will ultimately prevail.
*   **January 31**: WWII: The [Battle of Hill 170](/Battle_of_Hill_170) in the Burma Campaign concludes. British [3rd Commando Brigade](/3rd_Commando_Brigade) forces the [Imperial Japanese Army 54th Division](/54th_Division_(Imperial_Japanese_Army)) to withdraw, leading to the retreat of the [Japanese Twenty-Eighth Army](/Twenty-Eighth_Army_(Japan)) from the [Arakan](/Rakhine_State) Peninsula.

#### February

*   Main article: [February 1945](/February_1945)

*   **February (month)**: Raymond L. Libby of [American Cyanamid](/American_Cyanamid)'s research laboratories in [Stamford, Connecticut](/Stamford,_Connecticut), announces a breakthrough method for the oral administration of the antibiotic [penicillin](/Penicillin). &#91;8&#93;
*   **February 3**: WWII:
    *   The [Battle of Manila](/Battle_of_Manila_(1945)) commences as United States forces advance into the outskirts of [Manila](/Manila) to capture it from the [Japanese Imperial Army](/Imperial_Japanese_Army). On February 4, U.S. Army forces successfully liberate the [Santo Tomas Internment Camp](/Santo_Tomas_Internment_Camp) within the city.
    *   The [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union) reaffirms its commitment to enter the [Pacific War](/Pacific_War) against Japan once the conflict in Europe is resolved.
*   **February 4–11**: WWII: The [Yalta Conference](/Yalta_Conference) convenes, with [President](/President_of_the_United_States) [Franklin D. Roosevelt](/Franklin_D._Roosevelt), [Prime Minister of the United Kingdom](/Prime_Minister_of_the_United_Kingdom) [Winston Churchill](/Winston_Churchill), and [Soviet](/Soviet_Union) leader [Joseph Stalin](/Joseph_Stalin) meeting to discuss the post-war world order.
*   **February 7**: WWII: General [Douglas MacArthur](/Douglas_MacArthur) makes his return to [Manila](/Manila).
*   **February 8**: The Alaska Anti-Discrimination Act of 1945, strongly advocated for by the influential native leader [Elizabeth Peratrovich](/Elizabeth_Peratrovich), is passed by the territorial Senate, following the legislature's earlier rejection of a similar bill in 1943.
*   **February 9**:
    *   [Walter Ulbricht](/Walter_Ulbricht) assumes leadership of the German [Communists](/Communism) in Moscow.
    *   WWII: "Black Friday" occurs when a formation of Allied [Bristol Beaufighter](/Bristol_Beaufighter) aircraft sustains significant casualties during an unsuccessful assault on the German destroyer Z33 and its escorting vessels, which were harbored in [Førde Fjord](/F%C3%B8rde_Fjord), Norway.
*   **February 10**: WWII: The German [troopship](/Troopship) SS [General von Steuben](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SS_General_von_Steuben) is sunk by the Soviet submarine S-13, resulting in the deaths of 3,608 individuals. &#91;9&#93;
*   **February 10–20**: WWII: [Operation Kita](/Operation_Kita) sees the [Imperial Japanese Navy](/Imperial_Japanese_Navy) successfully return its "Completion Force," including its Ise-class battleships, from [Singapore](/Singapore) to [Kure](/Kure,_Hiroshima) amidst [Allied](/Allies_of_World_War_II) attacks.
*   **February 12**: A devastating tornado outbreak sweeps through [Mississippi](/Mississippi) and [Alabama](/Alabama), claiming 45 lives and injuring 427 people. &#91;10&#93; &#91;11&#93;
*   **February 13**: WWII:
    *   The [Budapest Offensive](/Budapest_Offensive) and the ensuing [Siege of Budapest](/Siege_of_Budapest) conclude with the surrender of [Budapest](/Budapest) (Hungary) to [Soviet](/Soviet_Union)-Romanian forces, marking the end of [Nazi](/Nazism) resistance in the city.
    *   The [Bombing of Dresden](/Bombing_of_Dresden_in_World_War_II) commences, carried out by the British [Royal Air Force](/Royal_Air_Force) and [United States Army Air Forces](/United_States_Army_Air_Forces). An estimated 25,000–35,000 people are believed to have died in the aerial assault.
*   **February 16**: WWII:
    *   The [Bombing of Wesel](/Bombing_of_Wesel_in_World_War_II) begins, resulting in the destruction of 97% of the town over a three-day period.
    *   American and Filipino ground forces land on [Corregidor](/Corregidor) Island in the [Philippines](/Philippines).
    *   Combined American and Filipino forces successfully recapture the [Bataan](/Bataan) Peninsula.
    *   [Venezuela](/Venezuela) declares war on Germany.
*   **February 18–March 5**: WWII: [Operation Encore](/Operation_Encore) is launched by American and Brazilian troops in Northern Italy. This successful limited offensive in the [Northern Apennines](/Northern_Apennines) serves to pave the way for the western sector of the [Allied Spring offensive](/Spring_1945_offensive_in_Italy). &#91;12&#93;
*   **February 19–20**: Approximately 980 (though the exact figure is debated) &#91;13&#93; Japanese soldiers perish as a result of an attack by saltwater [crocodiles](/Crocodile) on [Ramree Island](/Battle_of_Ramree_Island), Burma. &#91;14&#93;
*   **February 19**: WWII: The [Battle of Iwo Jima](/Battle_of_Iwo_Jima) commences with the landing of approximately 30,000 [United States Marines](/United_States_Marine_Corps) on the island of [Iwo Jima](/Iwo_Jima).
*   **February 21**: The final [V-2 rocket](/V-2_rocket) is launched from [Peenemünde](/Peenem%C3%BCnde).
*   **February 22**: WWII:
    *   [Italian Front](/Italian_Campaign_(World_War_II)): The [Battle of Monte Castello](/Battle_of_Monte_Castello) concludes after nearly three months of intense fighting. The [Brazilian Expeditionary Force](/Brazilian_Expeditionary_Force) successfully dislodges German forces from a strategically vital point in the [(Tuscan) North Apennines](/Apennine_Mountains), from which their artillery had been impeding the advance of the [British Eighth Army](/Eighth_Army_(United_Kingdom)) towards [Bologna](/Bologna).
    *   [Uruguay](/Uruguay) declares war on Germany and Japan.
*   **February 23**: WWII:
    *   The [Battle of Iwo Jima](/Battle_of_Iwo_Jima): A contingent of [United States Marines](/United_States_Marine_Corps) reaches the summit of [Mount Suribachi](/Mount_Suribachi) on the island and captures the iconic moment of raising the [American flag](/Flag_of_the_United_States). The photograph, [Raising the Flag on Iwo Jima](/Raising_the_Flag_on_Iwo_Jima), taken by [Joe Rosenthal](/Joe_Rosenthal), later receives a [Pulitzer Prize](/Pulitzer_Prize).
    *   The [11th Airborne Division](/11th_Airborne_Division_(United_States)), in conjunction with [Filipino](/Filipino_people) guerrillas, liberates the captives of the [Los Baños](/Los_Ba%C3%B1os,_Laguna) internment camp.
    *   The capital of the [Philippines](/Philippines), Manila, is liberated by combined American and Filipino ground forces. The suburb of [Intramuros](/Intramuros) suffers extensive devastation. &#91;15&#93;
    *   The German garrison stationed in [Poznań](/Pozna%C5%84) capitulates to [Red Army](/Red_Army) and Polish troops.
    *   The [Bombing of Pforzheim](/Bombing_of_Pforzheim_in_World_War_II) culminates in the heaviest of several bombing raids on the German city by Allied aircraft, conducted by the British [Royal Air Force](/Royal_Air_Force). The raid results in the deaths of up to 17,600 people, approximately 31.4% of the town's population, and destroys about 83% of its buildings, two-thirds of its total area, and between 80 and 100% of the inner city.
    *   [Turkey](/Turkey) formally enters the war, aligning itself with the [Allies](/Allies_of_World_War_II).
*   **February 24**: Egyptian premier [Ahmad Mahir Pasha](/Ahmad_Mahir_Pasha) is assassinated in Parliament shortly after declaring war on Germany and Japan.
*   **February 27**: The [Bombing of Mainz](/Bombing_of_Mainz_in_World_War_II) results in 1,209 confirmed fatalities, with 80% of the city destroyed.
*   **February 28**: In [Bucharest](/Bucharest), a significant demonstration erupts, during which a Bolshevik faction opens fire on both the army and protesters. In response, [Andrei Y. Vishinsky](/Andrei_Y._Vishinsky), the [USSR](/USSR)'s vice commissioner of foreign affairs and president of the Allied Control Commission for [Romania](/Romania), travels to Bucharest to compel [Nicolae Rădescu](/Nicolae_R%C4%83descu) to resign his premiership.

#### March

*   Main article: [March 1945](/March_1945)

*   **March 1**: President [Franklin D. Roosevelt](/Franklin_D._Roosevelt) delivers his final address to a [joint session of the United States Congress](/Joint_session_of_the_United_States_Congress), providing a report on the proceedings of the [Yalta Conference](/Yalta_Conference).
*   **March 2**:
    *   Former U.S. vice president [Henry A. Wallace](/Henry_A._Wallace) begins his tenure as [United States Secretary of Commerce](/United_States_Secretary_of_Commerce), serving under President [Franklin D. Roosevelt](/Franklin_D._Roosevelt).
    *   The rocket-propelled [Bachem Ba 349](/Bachem_Ba_349) Natter undergoes its first test launch at [Stetten am kalten Markt](/Stetten_am_kalten_Markt). The launch ends in failure, and the pilot, [Lothar Sieber](/Lothar_Sieber), loses his life. &#91;16&#93;
*   **March 3**: WWII:
    *   Finland formally declares war on the [Axis powers](/Axis_powers).
    *   United States and Filipino troops successfully capture [Manila](/Battle_of_Manila_(1945)), [Philippines](/Philippines).
    *   The [Pawłokoma massacre](/Paw%C5%82okoma_massacre) occurs, where a Polish [Home Army](/Home_Army) unit is responsible for the deaths of between 150 and 500 Ukrainian civilians in the Polish village of [Pawłokoma](/Paw%C5%82okoma).
    *   The [Bombing of the Bezuidenhout](/Bombing_of_the_Bezuidenhout) takes place when the British [Royal Air Force](/Royal_Air_Force) accidentally bombs the [Bezuidenhout](/Bezuidenhout) neighborhood in [The Hague](/The_Hague), Netherlands, resulting in 511 fatalities.
*   **March 4**:
    *   In the United Kingdom, [Princess Elizabeth](/Elizabeth_II) (who would later become Queen Elizabeth II) joins the [Auxiliary Territorial Service](/Auxiliary_Territorial_Service) (ATS) as a truck driver and mechanic in London.
    *   The Swiss cities of [Basel](/Basel) and [Zürich](/Z%C3%BCrich) are subjected to [accidental bombing](/Aerial_incidents_in_Switzerland_in_World_War_II) by the United States. &#91;17&#93;
*   **March 5**: WWII: Brazilian forces achieve the liberation of Castelnuovo ([Vergato](/Vergato)), marking the final operations of the Allied [Operation Encore](/Operation_Encore).
*   **March 6**:
    *   A government led by [Communists](/Communism) is established in [Romania](/Kingdom_of_Romania) under the leadership of [Petru Groza](/Petru_Groza), following intervention by the [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union).
    *   Resistance fighters manage to ambush and attempt to execute SS general [Hanns Albin Rauter](/Hanns_Albin_Rauter), who was known as the chief persecutor of the Dutch.
*   **March 7**: WWII: The conclusion of [Operation Lumberjack](/Operation_Lumberjack) sees American troops successfully seize the [Ludendorff Bridge](/Ludendorff_Bridge) spanning the [Rhine](/Rhine) at [Remagen](/Remagen), Germany, and commence crossing. Over the subsequent ten days, 25,000 troops along with their equipment are able to cross the river.
*   **March 8**:
    *   [Josip Broz Tito](/Josip_Broz_Tito) forms a [Provisional Government of the Democratic Federal Yugoslavia](/Provisional_Government_of_the_Democratic_Federal_Yugoslavia) within the [Kingdom of Yugoslavia](/Kingdom_of_Yugoslavia).
    *   Nazi authorities execute 117 Dutch men in retaliation for the attempted assassination of [Hanns Albin Rauter](/Hanns_Albin_Rauter).
    *   [Operation Sunrise](/Operation_Sunrise_(World_War_II)): [Waffen-SS](/Waffen-SS) General [Karl Wolff](/Karl_Wolff) meets with [Allen Welsh Dulles](/Allen_Welsh_Dulles) of the United States [Office of Strategic Services](/Office_of_Strategic_Services) in [Lucerne](/Lucerne), Switzerland, to negotiate the surrender of [Axis](/Axis_powers) forces in Italy to the [Allies](/Allies_of_World_War_II).
*   **March 9–10**: WWII: The [Bombing of Tokyo](/Bombing_of_Tokyo_(10_March_1945)) sees [USAAF](/USAAF) [B-29](/B-29_Superfortress) [bombers](/Bomber) launch an attack on Tokyo, Japan, employing [incendiary bombs](/Incendiary_device). The resulting firestorm claims the lives of 100,000 citizens, making it the single most destructive conventional air raid of the war.
*   **March 11**:
    *   The [Empire of Japan](/Empire_of_Japan) establishes the [Empire of Vietnam](/Empire_of_Vietnam), a [puppet state](/Puppet_state) that will exist only until August 23, with [Bảo Đại](/B%E1%BA%A3o_%C4%90%E1%BA%A1i) as its nominal ruler.
    *   The [Sammarinese general election](/1945_Sammarinese_general_election) results in [San Marino](/San_Marino) having the world's first democratically elected [communist](/Communist) government, which remains in power until [1957](/1957). &#91;18&#93; &#91;19&#93;
*   **March 12**: WWII: [Swinemünde](/Swinem%C3%BCnde) is devastated by the USAAF, with an estimated 8,000 to 23,000 civilian casualties, many of whom were refugees rescued during [Operation Hannibal](/Operation_Hannibal).
*   **March 15–31**: WWII: The Soviet [Red Army](/Red_Army) conducts the [Upper Silesian Offensive](/Upper_Silesian_Offensive).
*   **March 15**: The [17th Academy Awards](/17th_Academy_Awards) ceremony is held, marking the first time it is broadcast via radio in the United States. The award for [Best Picture](/Academy_Award_for_Best_Picture) goes to [Going My Way](/Going_My_Way).
*   **March 16**: WWII:
    *   The [Battle of Iwo Jima](/Battle_of_Iwo_Jima) unofficially concludes.
    *   The [Bombing of Würzburg](/Bombing_of_W%C3%BCrzburg_in_World_War_II), part of the Allied strategic bombing campaign against Nazi Germany, destroys 89% of the city and results in 4,000 deaths.
*   **March 17**: WWII: [Kobe](/Kobe), Japan, is subjected to firebombing by 331 [B-29](/B-29_Superfortress) bombers, causing over 8,000 fatalities.
*   **March 18**: WWII:
    *   The 40th Infantry Division, led by the 185th US Infantry Regiment, lands unopposed in [Tigbauan], prompting the surrender of Japanese forces and leading Generals [Macario Peralta](/Macario_Peralta) and Eichelberger to declare the [Liberation of Panay, Romblon and Guimaras](/Panay_Liberation_Day). &#91;20&#93;
    *   A total of 1,250 American bombers target Berlin. &#91;21&#93;
    *   The [Battle of Kolberg](/Battle_of_Kolberg_(1945)) concludes with the Baltic seaport, designated a key Festung (fortress) by the Germans, captured by Polish and Soviet forces. Ethnic Germans were either evacuated or expelled. &#91;22&#93;
*   **March 19**: WWII:
    *   [Adolf Hitler](/Adolf_Hitler) issues the "[Nero Decree](/Nero_Decree)," ordering the destruction of all industrial facilities, military installations, machine shops, transportation, and communication infrastructure within Germany as Allied forces advanced. However, [Albert Speer](/Albert_Speer), who was tasked with its implementation, deliberately disregarded the order.
    *   Off the coast of Japan, bombers inflict damage on the [aircraft carrier](/Aircraft_carrier) USS Franklin, resulting in the deaths of approximately 800 crew members and crippling the vessel.
*   **March 20**: WWII: Hitler dismisses [Heinrich Himmler](/Heinrich_Himmler) from his military command. &#91;3&#93;
*   **March 21**: WWII:
    *   British troops liberate [Mandalay](/Mandalay), [Burma](/British_rule_in_Burma).
    *   Bulgarian and Soviet forces successfully defend the northern bank of the [Drava River](/Drava_River) as the [Battle of the Transdanubian Hills](/Battle_of_the_Transdanubian_Hills) concludes.
*   **March 22**:
    *   The [Arab League](/Arab_League) is formally established with the adoption of its charter in [Cairo](/Cairo), Egypt.
    *   The [Hildesheim Cathedral](/Hildesheim_Cathedral) and the historic city center of [Hildesheim](/Hildesheim) in Germany are destroyed during a [bombing of the city](/Bombing_of_Hildesheim_in_World_War_II).
*   **March 24**:
    *   WWII: [Operation Varsity](/Operation_Varsity): Two airborne divisions successfully capture bridges across the river [Rhine](/Rhine), facilitating the Allied advance.
    *   The cartoon character [Sylvester the cat](/Sylvester_(Looney_Tunes)) makes his debut in [Life with Feathers](/Life_with_Feathers).
*   **March 26**: WWII: The [Battle of Iwo Jima](/Battle_of_Iwo_Jima) officially concludes, marked by the elimination of remaining Japanese resistance, although pockets of [Japanese holdouts](/Japanese_holdout) persisted on the island until 1949.
*   **March 27**: WWII:
    *   The [United States Army Air Forces](/United_States_Army_Air_Forces) initiates [Operation Starvation](/Operation_Starvation), deploying [naval mines](/Naval_mine) in numerous Japanese shipping lanes.
    *   [Argentina](/Argentina) declares war on [Germany](/Nazi_Germany) and [Japan](/Empire_of_Japan).
*   **March 29**:
    *   WWII: The [Red Army](/Red_Army) effectively annihilates the [German 4th Army](/4th_Army_(Wehrmacht)) within the [Heiligenbeil Pocket](/Heiligenbeil_Pocket) in [East Prussia](/East_Prussia).
    *   The "Clash of Titans" takes place: [George Mikan](/George_Mikan) and [Bob Kurland](/Bob_Kurland) face off at [Madison Square Garden](/Madison_Square_Garden_(1925)) in New York, where [Oklahoma State University](/Oklahoma_State_University%E2%80%93Stillwater) defeats [DePaul](/DePaul_University) 52–44 in a [basketball](/Basketball) game.
*   **March 30**: WWII:
    *   The [Red Army](/Red_Army) expels the majority of Axis forces from Hungary, pushing them into Austria.
    *   American official [Alger Hiss](/Alger_Hiss) receives commendation in Moscow for his role in fostering closer relations between the Western powers and the Soviet Union at the [Yalta Conference](/Yalta_Conference).

#### April

*   Main article: [April 1945](/April_1945)

*   **April 1**: WWII: The [Battle of Okinawa](/Battle_of_Okinawa) begins as the [Tenth United States Army](/Tenth_United_States_Army) lands on [Okinawa](/Okinawa_Prefecture).
*   **April 4**: WWII:
    *   American troops liberate their first Nazi concentration camp, [Ohrdruf extermination camp](/Ohrdruf_concentration_camp), located in Germany.
    *   The Soviet [Red Army](/Red_Army) advances into [Bratislava](/Bratislava) and pushes towards the outskirts of [Vienna](/Vienna), capturing the city on April 13 following several days of intense combat.
*   **April 6**: WWII:
    *   [Sarajevo](/Sarajevo) is liberated from [Nazi Germany](/Nazi_Germany) and the [Independent State of Croatia](/Independent_State_of_Croatia) (a [fascist](/Fascist) [puppet state](/Puppet_state)) by [Yugoslav Partisans](/Yugoslav_Partisans).
    *   The [Battle of Slater's Knoll](/Battle_of_Slater%27s_Knoll) on [Bougainville Island](/Bougainville_Island) concludes with a decisive victory for the [Australian Army](/Australian_Army)'s [7th Brigade](/7th_Brigade_(Australia)).
    *   Allied forces reach the [Merkers Salt Mines](/Merkers_Adventure_Mines) in [Thuringia](/Thuringia), discovering significant gold reserves belonging to the Nazi German [Reichsbank](/Reichsbank) and numerous art treasures.
*   **April 7**: WWII:
    *   The sole mission of the German ramming unit known as [Sonderkommando Elbe](/Sonderkommando_Elbe) takes place, resulting in the loss of approximately 24 [B-17s](/B-17_Flying_Fortress) and [B-24s](/B-24_Liberator) belonging to the United States [Eighth Air Force](/Eighth_Air_Force).
    *   The Japanese battleship [Yamato](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_battleship_Yamato) and nine other warships participate in [Operation Ten-Go](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Ten-Go), a suicide mission targeting Allied forces engaged in the Battle of Okinawa. The Yamato is sunk by U.S. Navy aircraft in the [East China Sea](/East_China_Sea), approximately 200 miles (320 km) north of [Okinawa](/Okinawa_Prefecture), with the loss of 2,055 of its 2,332 crew members, along with five other Japanese warships.
    *   [Kantarō Suzuki](/Kantar%C5%8D_Suzuki) assumes the position of [Prime Minister of Japan](/Prime_Minister_of_Japan).
*   **April 8**: The [SS](/SS) commences the evacuation of the [Buchenwald concentration camp](/Buchenwald_concentration_camp). Inmates involved in the [Buchenwald Resistance](/Buchenwald_Resistance) appeal for American assistance and subsequently overpower and kill the remaining guards.
*   **April 9**:
    *   WWII: The [Battle of Königsberg](/Battle_of_K%C3%B6nigsberg), fought in [East Prussia](/East_Prussia), concludes with Soviet forces capturing the city.
    *   [Abwehr](/Abwehr) conspirators [Wilhelm Canaris](/Wilhelm_Canaris), [Hans Oster](/Hans_Oster), and [Hans von Dohnányi](/Hans_von_Dohn%C3%A1nyi) are executed by hanging at Flossenberg concentration camp, alongside pastor [Dietrich Bonhoeffer](/Dietrich_Bonhoeffer).
    *   [Johann Georg Elser](/Johann_Georg_Elser), who had attempted to assassinate [Adolf Hitler](/Adolf_Hitler), is executed at [Dachau concentration camp](/Dachau_concentration_camp).
*   **April 10**: WWII: [Visoko](/Visoko) is liberated by the 7th, 9th, and 17th Krajina Brigades of the Tenth Division of [Yugoslav Partisan](/Yugoslav_Partisans) forces.
*   **April 11**: The [Buchenwald concentration camp](/Buchenwald_concentration_camp) is liberated by the [United States Army](/United_States_Army).
*   **April 12**:
    *   Vice President [Harry S. Truman](/Harry_S._Truman) ascends to the presidency, becoming the 33rd President of the United States, following the death of President [Franklin D. Roosevelt](/Franklin_D._Roosevelt) due to an [intracerebral hemorrhage](/Intracerebral_hemorrhage) at the [Little White House](/Little_White_House) in [Warm Springs, Georgia](/Warm_Springs,_Georgia). President Truman is [sworn in](/First_inauguration_of_Harry_S._Truman) later that evening in the [White House](/White_House).
    *   A severe tornado outbreak occurs across the United States, resulting in 128 fatalities and over 1,000 injuries. This event is largely overshadowed by the death of President Roosevelt. &#91;23&#93; &#91;24&#93;
    *   WWII: The [U.S. Ninth Army](/Ninth_United_States_Army), under the command of General [William H. Simpson](/William_H._Simpson), crosses the [Elbe River](/Elbe) near [Magdeburg](/Magdeburg) and reaches [Tangermünde](/Tangerm%C3%BCnde), positioning them just 50 miles from [Berlin](/Berlin).
    *   [Richard Strauss](/Richard_Strauss) completes the composition of his work [Metamorphosen](/Metamorphosen).
*   **April 14**: WWII:
    *   The [First Canadian Army](/First_Canadian_Army) assumes military oversight of the Netherlands, where German forces are entrenched within the Atlantic Wall fortifications along the coastline. &#91;25&#93;
    *   The [Razing of Friesoythe](/Razing_of_Friesoythe): The [4th Canadian (Armoured) Division](/4th_Canadian_(Armoured)_Division) deliberately destroys the German town of [Friesoythe](/Friesoythe) under orders from Major General [Christopher Vokes](/Christopher_Vokes).
*   **April 15**: WWII:
    *   The [Bergen-Belsen concentration camp](/Bergen-Belsen_concentration_camp) is liberated by British and Canadian forces.
    *   Canadian forces achieve the capture of [Arnhem](/Arnhem) in the northern [Netherlands], as the Canadian First Army reaches the coast.
*   **April 16**: WWII:
    *   The [Battle of Berlin](/Battle_of_Berlin) commences with a massive offensive by the [Red Army](/Red_Army), launching the [Battle of the Oder–Neisse](/Battle_of_the_Oder%E2%80%93Neisse) and the [Battle of the Seelow Heights](/Battle_of_the_Seelow_Heights).
    *   Canadian forces secure [Harlingen](/Harlingen,_Friesland) and occupy [Leeuwarden](/Leeuwarden) and [Groningen](/Groningen) in the Netherlands.
    *   The MV [Goya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MV_Goya) is sunk by the Soviet submarine L-3 in the [Baltic Sea](/Baltic_Sea) while engaged in the evacuation of German troops and civilians as part of [Operation Hannibal](/Operation_Hannibal). An estimated 7,000–8,000 individuals drown.
    *   [Death marches](/Death_marches_(Holocaust)) from [Flossenbürg concentration camp](/Flossenb%C3%BCrg_concentration_camp) commence.
*   **April 17**: WWII:
    *   [Battle of Montese](/Battle_of_Montese): Brazilian forces liberate the Italian town of [Montese](/Montese) from German control.
    *   The [Inundation of the Wieringermeer](/Inundation_of_the_Wieringermeer) in the Netherlands is carried out by occupying German forces.
*   **April 18**: American [war correspondent](/War_correspondent) [Ernie Pyle](/Ernie_Pyle) is killed by Japanese [machine gun](/Machine_gun) fire on the island of [Ie Shima](/Iejima) off the coast of [Okinawa](/Okinawa_Prefecture).
*   **April 19**: The musical play [Carousel](/Carousel_(musical)) by [Rodgers and Hammerstein](/Rodgers_and_Hammerstein), based on [Ferenc Molnár](/Ferenc_Moln%C3%A1r)'s play [Liliom](/Liliom), opens on [Broadway](/Broadway_theatre) and achieves significant success, becoming their second long-running stage classic. It features the well-known standard "[You'll Never Walk Alone](/You%27ll_Never_Walk_Alone)".
*   **April 20**: WWII:
    *   On his 56th birthday, [Adolf Hitler](/Adolf_Hitler) leaves his [Führerbunker](/F%C3%BChrerbunker) to decorate a group of [Hitler Youth](/Hitler_Youth) soldiers in Berlin. This marks his final excursion to the surface from his underground bunker.
    *   The German city of [Nuremberg](/Nuremberg), previously the site of the infamous [Nuremberg rallies](/Nuremberg_rallies), is occupied by American troops.
    *   The "[Morotai Mutiny](/Morotai_Mutiny)": Members of the [Australian First Tactical Air Force](/Australian_First_Tactical_Air_Force), stationed on the island of [Morotai](/Morotai) in the [Dutch East Indies](/Dutch_East_Indies), tender their resignations. They cite their belief that they are being assigned to missions of negligible military importance and outside their areas of expertise. A subsequent inquiry effectively vindicates their position. &#91;26&#93;
*   **April 22**: WWII:
    *   [Heinrich Himmler](/Heinrich_Himmler), through [Folke Bernadotte](/Folke_Bernadotte), Count of Wisborg, extends an offer of German surrender to the Western Allies, excluding the Soviet Union.
    *   [Adolf Hitler](/Adolf_Hitler) finally concedes that "everything is lost" &#91;27&#93; during a meeting in the Führerbunker, after learning that SS-Obergruppenführer [Felix Steiner](/Felix_Steiner) cannot mobilize sufficient forces for a counterattack against the [Soviet](/Soviet_Union) forces surrounding Berlin.
*   **April 23**: WWII:
    *   [Hermann Göring](/Hermann_G%C3%B6ring) dispatches the [Göring telegram](/G%C3%B6ring_telegram) to Hitler, requesting confirmation that he should assume leadership of Germany, in accordance with the decree issued on June 29, 1941. Hitler perceives this action as treason.
    *   The primary [Flossenbürg concentration camp](/Flossenb%C3%BCrg_concentration_camp) is liberated by the United States Army.
*   **April 24**: WWII:
    *   [Battle of Berlin](/Battle_of_Berlin): [Red Army](/Red_Army) troops complete the encirclement of Berlin. &#91;28&#93;
    *   Retreating [German troops](/Wehrmacht) demolish all bridges spanning the [Adige](/Adige) River in [Verona](/Verona), including the historic [Ponte di Castelvecchio](/Castelvecchio_Bridge) and [Ponte Pietra](/Ponte_Pietra_(Verona)).
*   **April 25**:
    *   Negotiations for the establishment of the [United Nations](/United_Nations) commence in [San Francisco](/San_Francisco).
    *   WWII – [Elbe Day](/Elbe_Day): United States and [Soviet](/Soviet_Union) troops establish contact at the river [Elbe](/Elbe), effectively dividing Germany into two.
*   **April 25–26**: WWII: The final major [strategic bombing](/Strategic_bombing) operation by [RAF Bomber Command](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RAF_Bomber_Command), targeting the oil refinery at [Tønsberg](/T%C3%B8nsberg) in southern Norway, is carried out by 107 [Avro Lancasters](/Avro_Lancaster).
*   **April 26**: WWII:
    *   [Battle of Bautzen](/Battle_of_Bautzen_(1945)): The last notably "successful" German panzer offensive concludes in [Bautzen](/Bautzen) with the recapture of the city.
    *   The [British 3rd Infantry Division](/3rd_Infantry_Division_(United_Kingdom)), under the command of [General Whistler](/Lashmer_Whistler), captures Bremen. &#91;29&#93;
    *   Due to German surrenders, the British and Canadians now control the German border with Switzerland, extending from [Basel](/Basel) to [Lake Constance](/Lake_Constance).
*   **April 27**:
    *   The last German formations withdraw from Finland into Norway. The [Lapland War](/Lapland_War) concludes, marking the end of [World War II in Finland](/Military_history_of_Finland_during_World_War_II). The photograph [Raising the Flag on the Three-Country Cairn](/Raising_the_Flag_on_the_Three-Country_Cairn) is taken on this day.
    *   The provisional government of [Austria](/Austria), led by [Karl Renner](/Karl_Renner), formally asserts its independence from Germany. &#91;30&#93;
    *   U.S. Ordnance troops discover the coffins of [Frederick William I of Prussia](/Frederick_William_I_of_Prussia), [Frederick the Great](/Frederick_the_Great), [Paul von Hindenburg](/Paul_von_Hindenburg) and his wife within a salt mine in Germany. &#91;31&#93;
*   **April 28**:
    *   The bodies of [Benito Mussolini](/Benito_Mussolini), his mistress [Clara Petacci](/Clara_Petacci), and other followers are publicly displayed, hung by their heels at a gasoline station in [Milan](/Milan)'s Piazzale Loreto, following their execution by Italian partisans as they attempted to flee the country.
    *   The Canadian First Army captures [Emden](/Emden) and [Wilhelmshaven](/Wilhelmshaven).
*   **April 29**:
    *   At the royal palace in [Caserta](/Caserta), Lieutenant-Colonel Viktor von Schweinitz (representing General [Heinrich von Vietinghoff](/Heinrich_von_Vietinghoff)) and SS-Obersturmbannführer Eugen Wenner (representing [Waffen-SS](/Waffen-SS) General [Karl Wolff](/Karl_Wolff)) sign an unconditional instrument of surrender for all [Axis powers](/Axis_powers) forces in Italy, which is to take effect on [May 2](/May_2). Italian General [Rodolfo Graziani](/Rodolfo_Graziani) orders the [Esercito Nazionale Repubblicano](/Esercito_Nazionale_Repubblicano) forces under his command to lay down their arms. &#91;32&#93;
    *   The [Dachau concentration camp](/Dachau_concentration_camp) is surrendered to U.S. forces, who subsequently kill SS guards at the camp and in the nearby hamlet of Webling. &#91;33&#93;
    *   Brazilian forces liberate the commune of [Fornovo di Taro](/Fornovo_di_Taro), Italy, from German occupation.
    *   [Operation Manna](/Operations_Manna_and_Chowhound): British [Avro Lancaster](/Avro_Lancaster) bombers drop essential food supplies into the Netherlands to alleviate the starvation of the civilian population.
    *   Soviet soldiers raise the [Red flag](/Red_flag_(politics)) over the [Reich Chancellery](/Reich_Chancellery) in Berlin.
    *   [Adolf Hitler](/Adolf_Hitler) marries his longtime mistress [Eva Braun](/Eva_Braun) in a private civil ceremony within the Berlin [Führerbunker](/F%C3%BChrerbunker), and signs [his last will and testament](/Last_will_and_testament_of_Adolf_Hitler).
*   **April 30**: WWII:
    *   [Death of Adolf Hitler](/Death_of_Adolf_Hitler): Adolf Hitler and his wife of one day, [Eva Braun](/Eva_Braun), commit suicide as [Red Army](/Red_Army) forces close in on the [Führerbunker](/F%C3%BChrerbunker) in Berlin. Großadmiral [Karl Dönitz](/Karl_D%C3%B6nitz) assumes the role of Reichspräsident (President of Germany), and [Joseph Goebbels](/Joseph_Goebbels) becomes Reichskanzler (Chancellor of Germany), as stipulated in Hitler's political testament from the previous day.
    *   American forces enter the Bavarian capital of [Munich](/Munich).

#### May

*   Main article: [May 1945](/May_1945)

*   **May (month)**: Marines of the 1st Marine Division are depicted [fighting on Okinawa](/Battle_of_Okinawa).
*   **May 1**: WWII:
    *   [Reichssender Hamburg](/Nordwestdeutscher_Rundfunk)'s [Flensburg](/Flensburg) radio station broadcasts the announcement that Hitler has died in battle, "fighting to his last breath against [Bolshevism](/Bolshevik)."
    *   [Joseph Goebbels](/Joseph_Goebbels) performs his only official act as Chancellor of Germany, dictating a letter to the Soviet commander in Berlin informing him of Hitler's death and requesting a ceasefire. Upon refusal, he and his wife [Magda](/Magda_Goebbels) commit suicide after killing their [six children](/Goebbels_children). Karl Dönitz appoints [Lutz Graf Schwerin von Krosigk](/Lutz_Graf_Schwerin_von_Krosigk) as the new de facto [Chancellor of Germany](/Chancellor_of_Germany), leading the [Flensburg Government](/Flensburg_Government).
    *   Troops of the [Yugoslav](/Socialist_Federal_Republic_of_Yugoslavia) 4th Army, along with the [Slovene](/Slovenes) 9th Corpus NOV, enter [Trieste](/Trieste).
    *   An estimated 700–2,500 suicides occur during the [Mass suicide in Demmin](/Mass_suicide_in_Demmin), following the destruction of 80% of the town by Soviet forces over the preceding three days.
*   **May 2**: WWII:
    *   The [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union) announces the [fall of Berlin](/Battle_of_Berlin). The iconic photograph of [Raising a Flag over the Reichstag](/Raising_a_Flag_over_the_Reichstag) is taken on this date.
    *   [Lübeck](/L%C3%BCbeck) is liberated by the [British Army](/British_Army).
    *   The surrender of [Axis troops](/Axis_powers) in Italy takes effect.
    *   A [Holocaust](/Holocaust) [death march](/Death_marches_(Holocaust)) from [Dachau](/Dachau_concentration_camp) towards the Austrian border is halted approximately two kilometers west of [Waakirchen](/Waakirchen) by the segregated, all-[Nisei](/Nisei) [522nd Field Artillery Battalion](/442nd_Infantry_Regiment_(United_States)) of the U.S. Army in southern Bavaria, saving several hundred prisoners. &#91;34&#93; &#91;35&#93;
    *   Troops of the [New Zealand Army](/New_Zealand_Army) [2nd Division](/2nd_Division_(New_Zealand)) enter [Trieste](/Trieste), one day after the [Yugoslavs](/Yugoslavs). The [German Army](/German_Army_(Wehrmacht)) in [Trieste](/Trieste) surrenders to the [New Zealand Army](/New_Zealand_Army).
    *   Following the death or resignation of the [Hitler Cabinet](/Hitler_Cabinet), the [Schwerin von Krosigk cabinet](/Schwerin_von_Krosigk_cabinet) convenes for the first time.
    *   The [Neuengamme concentration camp](/Neuengamme_concentration_camp) near [Hamburg](/Hamburg) is evacuated around this date.
    *   Expatriate American poet [Ezra Pound](/Ezra_Pound) is apprehended by the [Italian resistance movement](/Italian_resistance_movement) but is soon released due to a lack of interest. On [May 5](/May_5), he surrenders himself to the [United States Army](/United_States_Army) and is imprisoned on charges of treason.
*   **May 3**: WWII:
    *   The [prison ships](/Prison_ship) [Cap Arcona](/Cap_Arcona) (5,000 dead), [Thielbek](/SS_Thielbek_(1940)) (2,750 dead), and [Deutschland](/SS_Deutschland_(1923)) (all survivors) are sunk by the British [Royal Air Force](/Royal_Air_Force) in [Lübeck](/L%C3%BCbeck) Bay.
    *   Rocket scientist [Wernher von Braun](/Wernher_von_Braun) and 120 members of his team surrender to U.S. forces, later playing a pivotal role in the commencement of the U.S. space program.
    *   German Protestant theologian [Gerhard Kittel](/Gerhard_Kittel) is arrested by French forces in Tübingen, Germany.
    *   [Operation Dracula](/Operation_Dracula): British troops liberate the Burmese capital of [Rangoon](/Rangoon) from Japanese forces.
*   **May 4**: WWII:
    *   [German surrender at Lüneburg Heath](/German_surrender_at_L%C3%BCneburg_Heath): All German armed forces operating in northwest Germany, Denmark, and the Netherlands surrender unconditionally to Field Marshal [Bernard Montgomery](/Bernard_Montgomery,_1st_Viscount_Montgomery_of_Alamein), effective May 5 at 08:00 hours British Double (and German) Summer Time.
    *   The Netherlands is liberated by British and Canadian troops. &#91;36&#93;
    *   Denmark is liberated. &#91;37&#93;
    *   Admiral [Karl Dönitz](/Karl_D%C3%B6nitz) orders all [U-boats](/U-boat) to cease offensive operations and return to their bases in Norway. &#91;38&#93;
    *   The [Holy Crown of Hungary](/Holy_Crown_of_Hungary) is discovered in [Mattsee](/Mattsee), Austria, by the [United States Army 86th Infantry Division](/86th_Infantry_Division_(United_States)). The U.S. government retains custody of the crown at [Fort Knox](/Fort_Knox) to safeguard it from the Soviets until its return to [Hungary](/Hungary) on January 6 [1978](/1978). &#91;39&#93;
    *   The German auxiliary cruiser [Orion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_cruiser_Orion) sinks while en route to [Copenhagen](/Copenhagen), carrying refugees, resulting in over 3,800 lives lost.
*   **May 5**: WWII:
    *   The [Prague uprising](/Prague_uprising) begins as [Prague](/Prague) revolts against occupying Nazi forces, spurred by radio broadcasts (giving rise to the [Battle for Czech Radio](/Battle_for_Czech_Radio)).
    *   The [US 11th Armored Division](/11th_Armored_Division_(United_States)) liberates the prisoners of [Mauthausen concentration camp](/Mauthausen-Gusen_concentration_camp), including [Simon Wiesenthal](/Simon_Wiesenthal).
    *   Canadian soldiers liberate the city of [Amsterdam](/Amsterdam) from [Nazi](/Nazism) occupation.
    *   A Japanese [fire balloon](/Fire_balloon) causes the deaths of six individuals, Elsie Mitchell and five children, near [Bly, Oregon](/Bly,_Oregon), when it explodes as they attempt to move it from the woods. These are the only fatalities attributed to enemy action on the American mainland during WWII.
*   **May 6**:
    *   WWII: [Mildred Gillars](/Mildred_Gillars), known as "Axis Sally," delivers her final [propaganda](/Propaganda) broadcast to [Allied](/Allies_of_World_War_II) troops (her first broadcast was on December 11, [1941](/1941)).
    *   [The Holocaust](/The_Holocaust): The [Ebensee concentration camp](/Ebensee_concentration_camp) in Austria is liberated by troops of the [80th Division (United States)](/80th_Division_(United_States)).
*   **May 6–7**: The government of the [Independent State of Croatia](/Independent_State_of_Croatia), a fascist puppet state affiliated with the Nazis and established in occupied [Yugoslavia](/Kingdom_of_Yugoslavia), flees [Zagreb](/Zagreb) for a location near [Klagenfurt](/Klagenfurt) in Austria. However, they are captured during the [Bleiburg repatriations](/Bleiburg_repatriations), which subsequently lead to mass executions. &#91;40&#93; &#91;41&#93;
*   **May 7**: WWII:
    *   At 02:41, General [Alfred Jodl](/Alfred_Jodl) signs the unconditional [German Instrument of Surrender](/German_Instrument_of_Surrender) at [SHAEF](/SHAEF) headquarters in [Reims](/Reims), France, officially ending Germany's participation in the war. The surrender becomes effective on May 8 at 23:01 hours Central European Time (00:01 hours May 9 German Summer Time). This afternoon, [Lutz Graf Schwerin von Krosigk](/Lutz_Graf_Schwerin_von_Krosigk), the leading minister in the rump [Flensburg Government](/Flensburg_Government), makes a broadcast announcing the German surrender. American journalist [Edward Kennedy](/Edward_Kennedy_(journalist)) breaks the Allied news embargo on the signing. &#91;42&#93;
    *   Numerous RAF [Lancasters](/Avro_Lancaster) land in Germany to repatriate British prisoners of war. Approximately 4,500 ex-POWs are flown back to Great Britain over the following 24 hours.
*   **May 8**: WWII:
    *   [Victory in Europe Day](/Victory_in_Europe_Day) (VE Day) is observed by the western European powers as [Nazi Germany](/Nazi_Germany) formally surrenders, signifying the end of WWII in Europe.
    *   Shortly before midnight (May 9 Moscow time), the final [German Instrument of Surrender](/German_Instrument_of_Surrender) is signed at the headquarters of the Soviet Military Administration in Berlin-[Karlshorst](/Karlshorst), attended by representatives of the [Allies](/Allies_of_World_War_II).
    *   Canadian troops enter [Amsterdam](/Amsterdam) following the surrender of German troops.
    *   The surrender of the [Dodecanese](/Dodecanese) islands is signed in [Symi](/Symi).
    *   The [Prague uprising](/Prague_uprising) concludes with a ceasefire.
    *   The [Eighth British Army](/Eighth_Army_(United_Kingdom)), in conjunction with Slovene partisan troops and a motorized detachment of the Yugoslav 4th Army, arrives in [Carinthia](/Carinthia_(state)) and [Klagenfurt](/Klagenfurt). The [Croatian Armed Forces](/Croatian_Armed_Forces_(Independent_State_of_Croatia)) of the former puppet [Independent State of Croatia](/Independent_State_of_Croatia) receive orders from their commanders to avoid surrendering to the [Yugoslav Partisans](/Yugoslav_Partisans) and instead attempt to retreat into Austria and surrender to the British, a key event leading to the [Bleiburg repatriations](/Bleiburg_repatriations).
    *   [Hermann Göring](/Hermann_G%C3%B6ring) surrenders himself to the United States Army near [Radstadt](/Radstadt). &#91;43&#93;
*   **May 8–29**: The [Sétif and Guelma massacre](/S%C3%A9tif_and_Guelma_massacre) occurs in [Algeria](/Algeria). Thousands die as French troops and demobilized Italian POWs perpetrate mass killings of an estimated 6,000 to 40,000 Algerian citizens.
*   **May 9**: WWII:
    *   The [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union) observes [VE Day](/Victory_in_Europe_Day) as the [Red Army](/Red_Army) enters Prague. &#91;44&#93;
    *   [Vidkun Quisling](/Vidkun_Quisling) and other members of the [collaborationist](/Collaborationism) [Quisling regime](/Quisling_regime) in Norway surrender to the Resistance ([Milorg](/Milorg)) and [police](/Norwegian_police_troops_in_Sweden_during_World_War_II) at [Møllergata 19](/M%C3%B8llergata_19) in Oslo, as part of the post-war [legal purge in Norway after World War II](/Legal_purge_in_Norway_after_World_War_II).
    *   General [Alexander Löhr](/Alexander_L%C3%B6hr), Commander of German Army Group E near Topolšica, [Slovenia](/Slovenia), signs the capitulation of German occupation troops.
    *   [Liberation of the German-occupied Channel Islands](/Liberation_of_the_German-occupied_Channel_Islands): British forces accept the surrender of the occupying troops. Royal Navy ships HMS Bulldog arrives in [St Peter Port](/St_Peter_Port), [Guernsey](/Guernsey), and HMS Beagle in [St Helier](/St_Helier), [Jersey](/Jersey).
*   **May 10**: WWII: [Liberation of the German-occupied Channel Islands](/Liberation_of_the_German-occupied_Channel_Islands): Occupation of [Sark](/Sark) ends as British forces accept the surrender of the occupying troops, leaving them under the authority of Dame [Sibyl Hathaway](/Sibyl_Hathaway).
*   **May 12**:
    *   Argentinian labour leader José Peter announces the dissolution of the [Meat Industry Workers Federation](/Meat_Industry_Workers_Federation).
    *   Rev. [W. V. Awdry](/Wilbert_Awdry)'s children's book [The Three Railway Engines](/The_Three_Railway_Engines), the first in [The Railway Series](/The_Railway_Series), is published in England.
*   **May 14–15**: WWII: The [Battle of Poljana](/Battle_of_Poljana), the final engagement of the War in Europe, is fought at Poljana near [Slovenj Gradec](/Slovenj_Gradec), [Slovenia](/Slovenia).
*   **May 15**: WWII: [Surrender at Bleiburg](/Bleiburg_repatriations): Retreating troops of the [Croatian Armed Forces](/Croatian_Armed_Forces_(Independent_State_of_Croatia)) of the former puppet [Independent State of Croatia](/Independent_State_of_Croatia), intermingled with fleeing civilians, attempt to surrender to the British Army at [Bleiburg](/Bleiburg). They are redirected to surrender to [Yugoslav Partisans](/Yugoslav_Partisans), who subsequently open fire on them. The remaining individuals, acting under orders from [Tito](/Josip_Broz_Tito), are force-marched through Croatia and [Serbia](/Serbia), interned, or massacred, with thousands losing their lives. &#91;45&#93; &#91;46&#93;
*   **May 16**: WWII: [Liberation of the German-occupied Channel Islands](/Liberation_of_the_German-occupied_Channel_Islands): Occupation of [Alderney](/Alderney) concludes as British forces accept the surrender of the occupying troops. The civilian population had previously been evacuated.
*   **May 18**: WWII: [Operation Unthinkable](/Operation_Unthinkable): British prime minister [Winston Churchill](/Winston_Churchill) secretly instructs his military chiefs of staff to contemplate a plan involving British, American, and reactivated German forces to launch an attack on the [Soviet](/Soviet_Union) [Red Army](/Red_Army) on July 1, with the objective of preserving Poland's independence. The operation is deemed militarily unfeasible. &#91;47&#93; &#91;48&#93;
*   **May 23**:
    *   The [Flensburg Government](/Flensburg_Government) is dissolved by the Allies. [German president](/President_of_Germany_(1919%E2%80%931945)) [Karl Dönitz](/Karl_D%C3%B6nitz) and [German chancellor](/German_chancellor) [Lutz Graf Schwerin von Krosigk](/Lutz_Graf_Schwerin_von_Krosigk) are arrested by British [RAF Regiment](/RAF_Regiment) personnel at [Flensburg](/Flensburg). They served as the last German [head of state](/Head_of_state) and [head of government](/Prime_minister), respectively, until [1949](/1949).
    *   [Heinrich Himmler](/Heinrich_Himmler), the former head of the [Nazi](/Nazism) [SS](/Schutzstaffel), commits suicide while in British custody.
*   **May 28**: U.S.-born, Irish-raised [William Joyce](/William_Joyce), known as "[Lord Haw-Haw](/Lord_Haw-Haw)", is apprehended near the German border. He is subsequently charged in London with high treason for his wartime broadcasts in English from German radio, convicted, and ultimately hanged in January 1946.
*   **May 29**:
    *   German communists, under the leadership of [Walter Ulbricht](/Walter_Ulbricht), arrive in Berlin.
    *   Dutch painter [Han van Meegeren](/Han_van_Meegeren) is arrested on charges of collaboration with the Nazis. However, the "Dutch Golden Age" paintings he had sold to [Hermann Göring](/Hermann_G%C3%B6ring) are later proven to be his own forgeries.
*   **May 30**: The [Iranian](/Iran) government formally demands the withdrawal of all Soviet and British troops from the country.

#### June

*   Main article: [June 1945](/June_1945)

*   **June 1**: British forces assume control of [Lebanon](/Lebanon) and [Syria](/Syria).
*   **June 5**: The [Allied Control Council](/Allied_Control_Council), the military occupation authority governing Germany, formally assumes its powers.
*   **June 7**: King [Haakon VII of Norway](/Haakon_VII_of_Norway) returns to Norway, exactly five years after his departure into exile in Britain.
*   **June 11**:
    *   [William Lyon Mackenzie King](/William_Lyon_Mackenzie_King) is re-elected as Canadian prime minister.
    *   The Franck Committee recommends against the immediate use of a surprise nuclear bombing on Japan. &#91;49&#93;
*   **June 12**: The [Yugoslav](/Socialist_Federal_Republic_of_Yugoslavia) Army withdraws from [Trieste](/Trieste), leaving the [New Zealand Army](/New_Zealand_Army) in control of the city.
*   **June 21**: WWII: The [Battle of Okinawa](/Battle_of_Okinawa) concludes, with the United States maintaining its occupation of the island until [1972](/1972).
*   **June 24**: WWII: A significant [victory parade](/Moscow_Victory_Parade_of_1945) is held in [Red Square](/Red_Square) in Moscow.
*   **June 25**: [Seán T. O'Kelly](/Se%C3%A1n_T._O%27Kelly) is elected as the second [president of Ireland](/President_of_Ireland).
*   **June 26**: The [United Nations Charter](/United_Nations_Charter) is officially signed in San Francisco.
*   **June 29**: [Czechoslovakia](/Czechoslovakia) cedes [Carpathian Ruthenia](/Carpathian_Ruthenia) to the [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union).
*   **June 30**: [John von Neumann](/John_von_Neumann)'s seminal work, [First Draft of a Report on the EDVAC](/First_Draft_of_a_Report_on_the_EDVAC), is distributed. This document contains the first published description of the logical design of a computer, introducing the concept of a [stored-program](/Stored-program_computer) where instruction data is stored in the same address space within the memory, forming the basis of the [von Neumann architecture](/Von_Neumann_architecture).

#### July

*   Main article: [July 1945](/July_1945)

*   **July 1**:
    *   WWII: Germany is formally [divided](/Inner_German_border) into occupation zones administered by the Allied forces.
    *   WWII: Australian and other Allied forces commence an invasion of the east coast of Japanese-occupied [Borneo](/Borneo), near [Balikpapan](/Balikpapan).
*   **July 2**: The [1945 Sheikh Bashir rebellion](/1945_Sheikh_Bashir_rebellion) erupts in [Burao](/Burao) and [Erigavo](/Erigavo) in [British Somaliland](/British_Somaliland), led by [Sheikh Bashir](/Sheikh_Bashir), a prominent [Somali](/Somalis) religious leader. &#91;50&#93;
*   **July 4**: The Brazilian cruiser [Bahia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazilian_cruiser_Bahia) sinks due to an accidentally induced explosion, causing the deaths of over 300 personnel and leaving survivors adrift in shark-infested waters.
*   **July 5**:
    *   The [1945 United Kingdom general election](/1945_United_Kingdom_general_election) is held. However, polling in some constituencies is delayed due to local holiday schedules. The counting of votes and announcement of results are postponed until July 26 to accommodate the voting of a large number of service personnel still stationed overseas.
    *   [John Curtin](/John_Curtin), the 14th [Prime Minister of Australia](/Prime_Minister_of_Australia), dies in office from heart failure at the age of 60. He is briefly succeeded by his deputy, [Frank Forde](/Frank_Forde), who serves as the 15th Prime Minister until a [Labor Party](/Australian_Labor_Party) [leadership election](/1945_Australian_Labor_Party_leadership_election) is conducted to replace Curtin.
    *   WWII: The [Philippines](/Philippines) are officially declared liberated.
*   **July 6–7**: The [Schio massacre](/Schio_massacre) occurs, where 54 prisoners, predominantly fascist sympathizers, are killed by members of the [Italian resistance movement](/Italian_resistance_movement) in [Schio](/Schio).
*   **July 8**: WWII: President [Harry S. Truman](/Harry_S._Truman) is informed that Japan is amenable to peace talks if it can retain the imperial reign of the Emperor. &#91;49&#93;
*   **July 12**: [Ben Chifley](/Ben_Chifley) is elected leader of the [Labor Party](/Australian_Labor_Party), consequently becoming the 16th [Prime Minister of Australia](/Prime_Minister_of_Australia). He defeats [Frank Forde](/Frank_Forde) as well as [Norman Makin](/Norman_Makin) and [H.V. Evatt](/H.V._Evatt). This outcome results in Forde serving as the shortest-serving prime minister in Australian history, although he retains his position as deputy leader.
*   **July 14**: WWII: Italy formally declares war on Japan.
*   **July 16**:
    *   The [Trinity Test](/Trinity_(nuclear_test)), the first detonation of an [atomic bomb](/Nuclear_weapon), utilizing approximately six kilograms of [plutonium](/Plutonium), successfully unleashes an explosion equivalent to 22 kilotons of TNT.
    *   A train collision near [Munich](/Munich), Germany, results in the deaths of 102 prisoners of war.
*   **July 17–August 2**: WWII: The [Potsdam Conference](/Potsdam_Conference) takes place. At [Potsdam](/Potsdam), the three principal [Allied](/Allies_of_World_War_II) leaders convene for their final wartime summit. President Truman officially informs Stalin of the United States' possession of a formidable new weapon.
*   **July 21**: WWII: President [Harry S. Truman](/Harry_S._Truman) approves the directive for the use of atomic bombs against Japan. &#91;49&#93;
*   **July 23**: WWII: French marshal [Philippe Pétain](/Philippe_P%C3%A9tain), who led the [Vichy government](/Vichy_France) during WWII, stands trial for treason.
*   **July 26**:
    *   [Winston Churchill](/Winston_Churchill) resigns as [Prime Minister of the United Kingdom](/Prime_Minister_of_the_United_Kingdom) after his [Conservative Party](/Conservative_Party_(UK)) suffers a decisive defeat by the [Labour Party](/Labour_Party_(UK)) in the [1945 general election](/1945_United_Kingdom_general_election). [Clement Attlee](/Clement_Attlee) assumes the role of the new prime minister. This marks the first instance of the Labour Party governing Britain with a majority in the [House of Commons](/House_of_Commons_of_the_United_Kingdom). &#91;51&#93;
    *   The [Potsdam Declaration](/Potsdam_Declaration) is issued, demanding Japan's unconditional surrender. Notably, Article 12, which permitted Japan to retain the Emperor's reign, was omitted by President Truman. &#91;49&#93;
*   **July 27**: WWII: The [Bombing of Aomori](/Bombing_of_Aomori_in_World_War_II) occurs. Two [USAAF](/USAAF) [B-29s](/B-29_Superfortress) drop a total of 60,000 [leaflets](/Airborne_leaflet_propaganda) over the city of [Aomori](/Aomori_(city)), Japan, warning civilians of an impending air raid and urging their immediate evacuation. The city was subsequently firebombed the following day, resulting in over 1,700 deaths.
*   **July 28**:
    *   WWII: Japan issues an ambiguous rejection of the [Potsdam Declaration](/Potsdam_Declaration). &#91;49&#93;
    *   A [North American B-25 Mitchell](/North_American_B-25_Mitchell) aircraft crashes into [The Empire State Building](/Empire_State_Building), causing the deaths of 14 individuals. &#91;52&#93;
*   **July 29**:
    *   The [BBC Light Programme](/BBC_Light_Programme) radio station is launched in the United Kingdom, focusing on mainstream light entertainment and [music](/Music).
    *   WWII: The [Bombing of Aomori](/Bombing_of_Aomori_in_World_War_II) continues. The Japanese city of [Aomori](/Aomori_(city)) is firebombed by 63 [USAAF](/USAAF) [B-29](/B-29_Superfortress) [heavy bombers](/Heavy_bomber), resulting in 1,767 civilian deaths and the destruction of 18,045 homes.
*   **July 30**: WWII: The heavy cruiser USS [Indianapolis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_Indianapolis_(CA-35)) is struck and sunk by torpedoes from the Japanese submarine [I-58](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_submarine_I-58) in the [Philippine Sea](/Philippine_Sea). Approximately 900 survivors are left adrift for up to four days, with nearly 600 perishing before rescue arrived. Captain [Charles B. McVay III](/Charles_B._McVay_III) of the cruiser is later court-martialed and convicted; in 2000, he is posthumously exonerated. &#91;53&#93;

#### August

*   Main article: [August 1945](/August_1945)

*   **August 6**: WWII: The [Atomic bombing of Hiroshima](/Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki) occurs. The United States [Boeing B-29 Superfortress](/Boeing_B-29_Superfortress) named "[Enola Gay](/Enola_Gay)" drops a [uranium-235](/Uranium-235) [atomic bomb](/Atomic_bomb), codenamed "[Little Boy](/Little_Boy)", on the Japanese city of [Hiroshima](/Hiroshima) at 8:15 a.m. local time, causing an estimated 90,000 to 146,000 deaths.
*   **August 7**: U.S. President Harry Truman announces the successful atomic bombing of Hiroshima while returning from the Potsdam Conference aboard the U.S. Navy heavy cruiser USS [Augusta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_Augusta_(CA-31)), in the mid-Atlantic Ocean.
*   **August 8**:
    *   The [United Nations Charter](/United_Nations_Charter) is ratified by the United States Senate, making the nation the third to join the newly formed international organization.
    *   WWII: The Soviet Union declares war on Japan.
*   **August 9**: WWII:
    *   The [Atomic bombing of Nagasaki](/Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki) occurs. The United States [B-29](/Boeing_B-29_Superfortress) [Bockscar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bockscar) drops a [plutonium-239](/Plutonium-239) atomic bomb, codenamed "[Fat Man](/Fat_Man)", on the Japanese city of [Nagasaki](/Nagasaki) at 11:02 a.m. local time, resulting in an estimated 39,000 to 80,000 deaths.
    *   The [Soviet–Japanese War](/Soviet%E2%80%93Japanese_War) commences. The [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union) launches its army offensive against Japan in the northern sector of the Japanese-held Chinese region of [Manchuria](/Manchuria). &#91;54&#93;
*   **August 10**: WWII: Japan offers to surrender to the Allies, stipulating "provided this does not prejudice the sovereignty of the Emperor."
*   **August 11**:
    *   WWII: The [Allies](/Allies_of_World_War_II) respond to the Japanese surrender offer by stating that Emperor [Hirohito](/Hirohito) will be subject to the authority of the [Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces](/Supreme_Allied_Commander).
    *   [The Holocaust](/The_Holocaust): The [Kraków pogrom](/Krak%C3%B3w_pogrom) occurs, with [Róża Berger](/R%C3%B3%C5%Bca_Berger) being shot and killed by Polish militia.
*   **August 11–25**: Soviet troops complete their occupation of [Sakhalin](/Sakhalin).
*   **August 13**: The [Zionist](/Zionism) World Congress approaches the British government to discuss the establishment of the state of [Israel](/Israel).
*   **August 14**: WWII: Emperor [Hirohito](/Hirohito) accepts the terms of the [Potsdam Declaration](/Potsdam_Declaration). His recorded announcement of this decision is smuggled out of the [Tokyo Imperial Palace](/Tokyo_Imperial_Palace). At 19:00 hrs in [Washington, D.C.](/Washington,_D.C.) (23:00 [GMT](/GMT)), U.S. president [Harry S. Truman](/Harry_S._Truman) announces the Japanese surrender.
*   **August 15**: WWII:
    *   The [Bombing of Kumagaya](/Bombing_of_Kumagaya_in_World_War_II), Japan, is carried out by the United States using conventional bombs, commencing at 00:23.
    *   The [Hirohito surrender broadcast](/Hirohito_surrender_broadcast) (Gyokuon-hōsō): Emperor [Hirohito](/Hirohito)'s announcement of the unconditional [surrender of Japan](/Surrender_of_Japan) is broadcast on the radio shortly after noon (12:00 [Japan Standard Time](/Japan_Standard_Time), which is 03:00 GMT). This is likely the first time an [Emperor of Japan](/Emperor_of_Japan) has been heard by the general populace. Delivered in formal [classical Japanese](/Classical_Japanese_language), without directly mentioning surrender and following official censorship regarding the nation's weakened position, the recorded speech is not immediately comprehensible to ordinary people. The Allies designate this day as [Victory over Japan Day](/Victory_over_Japan_Day) (V-J Day). This event marks the end of the period of [Japanese expansionism](/Japanese_militarism), initiates the era of the [Occupation of Japan](/Occupation_of_Japan), and sets the stage for Korean independence.
    *   The [August Revolution](/August_Revolution) in [Vietnam](/Vietnam) begins, with the [Viet Minh](/Viet_Minh) seizing control of the capital, [Hanoi](/Hanoi), capitalizing on the collapse of Japanese authority.
    *   The Provisional [International Civil Aviation Organization](/International_Civil_Aviation_Organization) is established as a specialized agency of the [United Nations](/United_Nations).
*   **August 17**:
    *   Philippines President [José P. Laurel](/Jose_P._Laurel) issues an Executive Proclamation formally ending the [Second Philippine Republic](/Second_Philippine_Republic), thus concluding his term as President of the Philippines.
    *   The [Proclamation of Indonesian Independence](/Proclamation_of_Indonesian_Independence) is made by Indonesian nationalists [Sukarno](/Sukarno) and [Mohammad Hatta](/Mohammad_Hatta), who declare the independence of the Republic of [Indonesia](/Indonesia). Sukarno assumes the presidency with Mohammad Hatta as vice-president, sparking the [Indonesian National Revolution](/Indonesian_National_Revolution) against the [Dutch Empire](/Dutch_Empire).
*   **August 18**: WWII: [Death of Subhas Chandra Bose](/Death_of_Subhas_Chandra_Bose): Indian nationalist leader [Subhas Chandra Bose](/Subhas_Chandra_Bose) dies as a result of his overloaded Japanese aircraft crashing in [Japanese Taiwan](/Taiwan_under_Japanese_rule).
*   **August 19**: [Chinese Civil War](/Chinese_Civil_War): [Mao Zedong](/Mao_Zedong) and [Chiang Kai-shek](/Chiang_Kai-shek) meet in [Chongqing](/Chongqing) to discuss a cessation of hostilities between the [Communists](/Chinese_Communist_Party) and the [Nationalists](/Kuomintang).
*   **August 23**: [Soviet–Japanese War](/Soviet%E2%80%93Japanese_War): [Joseph Stalin](/Joseph_Stalin) orders the detention of [Japanese prisoners of war in the Soviet Union](/Japanese_prisoners_of_war_in_the_Soviet_Union).
*   **August 25**: [Bảo Đại](/B%E1%BA%A3o_%C4%90%E1%BA%A1i) abdicates his position as [Emperor of Vietnam](/Emperor_of_Vietnam), marking the end of 2,000 years of dynastic and monarchical rule in the country and 143 years of the [Nguyễn dynasty](/Nguy%E1%BB%85n_dynasty).
*   **August 30**: WWII: [Vietnam](/Vietnam)'s capital, [Hanoi](/Hanoi), is captured by the [Viet Minh](/Viet_Minh), which signifies the end of French occupation in what becomes [North Vietnam](/North_Vietnam), with the southern provinces subsequently designated as [South Vietnam](/South_Vietnam). This event concludes the [August Revolution](/August_Revolution).
*   **August 31**:
    *   WWII: Allied troops arrest German [field marshal](/Field_marshal) [Walther von Brauchitsch](/Walther_von_Brauchitsch).
    *   A team at [American Cyanamid](/American_Cyanamid)'s Lederle Laboratories in [Pearl River, New York](/Pearl_River,_New_York), led by [Yellapragada Subbarow](/Yellapragada_Subbarow), announces the successful isolation of [folic acid](/Folic_acid) in a pure crystalline form. &#91;55&#93; This essential [vitamin](/Vitamin) is known to be abundant in green [leaf vegetables](/Leaf_vegetable), [liver](/Liver), [kidney](/Kidney), and [yeast](/Yeast). &#91;56&#93;

#### September

*   Main article: [September 1945](/September_1945)

*   **September 2**: WWII concludes:
    *   Japanese general [Tomoyuki Yamashita](/Tomoyuki_Yamashita) formally surrenders to Philippine and American forces at [Kiangan, Ifugao](/Kiangan,_Ifugao).
    *   The final official [Japanese Instrument of Surrender](/Japanese_Instrument_of_Surrender) is accepted by Supreme Allied Commander General [Douglas MacArthur](/Douglas_MacArthur) and [Fleet Admiral](/Admiral_of_the_Fleet) [Chester W. Nimitz](/Chester_W._Nimitz) on behalf of the United States. Delegates from the United Kingdom, Australia, New Zealand, the Netherlands, China, and other nations were also present, representing a Japanese delegation led by [Mamoru Shigemitsu](/Mamoru_Shigemitsu), aboard the American battleship USS [Missouri](/USS_Missouri_(BB-63)) in [Tokyo Bay](/Tokyo_Bay).
    *   General [Douglas MacArthur](/Douglas_MacArthur) is bestowed the title of [Supreme Commander Allied Powers](/Supreme_Commander_Allied_Powers) and is also assigned the responsibility for the occupation of Japan. &#91;57&#93;
    *   The [Democratic Republic of Vietnam](/North_Vietnam) is officially established by [Ho Chi Minh](/Ho_Chi_Minh). &#91;57&#93;
*   **September 4**: WWII: Japanese forces surrender on [Wake Island](/Wake_Island) after receiving confirmation of their country's surrender.
*   **September 5**:
    *   [Iva Toguri D'Aquino](/Iva_Toguri_D%27Aquino), a [Japanese American](/Japanese_American) suspected of being the wartime radio propagandist "[Tokyo Rose](/Tokyo_Rose)", is arrested in [Yokohama](/Yokohama).
    *   Russian code clerk [Igor Gouzenko](/Igor_Gouzenko) presents documents implicating the Soviet Union in numerous spy rings operating across North America, in both the United States and Canada.
*   **September 8**:
    *   U.S. troops arrive in [Southern Korea](/United_States_Army_Military_Government_in_Korea), while the [Soviet Union](/Soviet_Union) occupies the [north](/Soviet_Civil_Authority). The dividing line is established at the 38th parallel of latitude. This arrangement inadvertently marks the beginning of a divided Korea, which would ultimately lead to the [Korean War](/Korean_War) following North Korea's invasion in [1950](/1950).
    *   The Afghan government successfully suppresses a rebel force at [Kunar Khas](/Siege_of_Kunar_Khas). Gerald Crichton, the British [Charge de 'affaires](/Charg%C3%A9_d%27affaires) in Kabul, later characterizes this victory as the "turning point" of the [Afghan tribal revolts of 1944–1947](/Afghan_tribal_revolts_of_1944%E2%80%931947). &#91;58&#93;
*   **September 9**:
    *   Chairman of the Nationalist Government of China, [Chiang Kai-shek](/Chiang_Kai-shek), formally accepts the Japanese capitulation in [Nanking](/Nanjing). &#91;57&#93;
    *   Japanese troops in [Keijō](/Keij%C5%8D) (present-day [Seoul](/Seoul)) formally relinquish control over Southern Korea to the United States, effectively ending Japan's 35-year rule over Korea. &#91;59&#93; &#91;60&#93;
*   **September 10**: [Vidkun Quisling](/Vidkun_Quisling) is sentenced to death in Norway for collaboration with the Nazis. &#91;57&#93;
*   **September 11**:
    *   [Hideki Tojo](/Hideki_Tojo), who served as Japanese prime minister for much of World War II, attempts suicide to evade facing an Allied [war crimes](/War_crime) tribunal.
    *   [Radio Republik Indonesia](/Radio_Republik_Indonesia) commences broadcasting.
    *   The [Batu Lintang camp](/Batu_Lintang_camp) in [Sarawak](/Sarawak), [Borneo](/Borneo), is liberated by Australian forces.
*   **September 12**:
    *   [Operation Tiderace](/Operation_Tiderace): The Japanese Army formally surrenders to the British in [Singapore](/Singapore).
    *   The office of [governor-general of Korea](/Governor-General_of_Ch%C5%8Dsen) is dissolved by the United States Army Military Government in Korea, formally ending Japan's 35-year administration of Korea.
*   **September 18**:
    *   [Typhoon Makurazaki](/Tropical_cyclone) causes widespread devastation in Japan, resulting in 3,746 fatalities.
    *   The Japanese Army in Central China officially surrenders to Chinese forces in [Wuhan](/Wuhan).
*   **September 20**: [Mohandas Gandhi](/Mahatma_Gandhi) and [Jawaharlal Nehru](/Jawaharlal_Nehru) issue a demand for the immediate withdrawal of all British troops from India.
*   **September 24**: [Postwar anti-Jewish violence in Slovakia](/Postwar_anti-Jewish_violence_in_Slovakia): The [Topoľčany pogrom](/Topo%C4%BE%C4%8Dany_pogrom) takes place in Czechoslovakia.
*   **October 1**: [Arthur C. Clarke](/Arthur_C._Clarke) introduces the concept of a [geosynchronous](/Geosynchronous_satellite) [communications satellite](/Communications_satellite) in an article published in [Wireless World](/Wireless_World) magazine.
*   **October 1–15**: [Operation Backfire](/Operation_Backfire_(WWII)): Three [A4 rockets](/V-2_rocket) are launched near [Cuxhaven](/Cuxhaven) as a demonstration for Allied forces.
*   **October 2**: [George Albert Smith](/George_Albert_Smith) becomes the [president](/President_of_the_Church_(LDS_Church)) of [the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints](/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints).
*   **October 4**: The [Partizan Belgrade](/Partizan_Belgrade) [sports club](/Sports_club) is founded in [Belgrade](/Belgrade), [Serbia](/Serbia).
*   **October 5**: [Hollywood Black Friday](/Hollywood_Black_Friday): A strike initiated by the Set Decorator's Union in Hollywood escalates into a riot.
*   **October 8–15**: The Hadamar Trial commences. Personnel from the [Hadamar Euthanasia Centre](/Hadamar_Euthanasia_Centre), now located within the American zone of [Allied-occupied Germany](/Allied-occupied_Germany), become the first individuals to be tried for systematic extermination in [Nazi Germany](/Nazi_Germany).
*   **October 9**: Former prime minister [Pierre Laval](/Pierre_Laval) is sentenced to death for his collaboration with the [Nazis](/Nazi) in [Vichy France](/Vichy_France). &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 10**: The [Nazi Party](/Nazi_Party) is officially dissolved by the Allied Powers.
*   **October 14**: [Czechoslovakia](/Czechoslovakia): A new provisional national assembly is elected. &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 15–21**: The [Fifth Pan-African Congress](/Pan-African_Congress) is convened in [Manchester](/Manchester).
*   **October 16**: The [Food and Agriculture Organization](/Food_and_Agriculture_Organization) is established following a meeting in [Quebec City](/Quebec_City), functioning as a specialized agency of the [United Nations](/United_Nations).
*   **October 17**: A large gathering of people, organized by the [General Confederation of Labour (Argentina)](/General_Confederation_of_Labour_(Argentina)), convenes in the [Plaza de Mayo](/Plaza_de_Mayo) in [Buenos Aires](/Buenos_Aires) to demand the release of [Juan Perón](/Juan_Per%C3%B3n). This event is recognized by [Peronists](/Peronism) as Día de la lealtad ([Loyalty Day](/Loyalty_Day_(Argentina))) and is considered the founding day of [Peronism](/Peronism).
*   **October 18**: [Isaías Medina Angarita](/Isa%C3%ADas_Medina_Angarita), president of [Venezuela](/Venezuela), is overthrown in a [military coup](/Coup_d%27%C3%A9tat). &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 19**: Members of the [Indonesian People's Army](/Indonesian_National_Armed_Forces) launch an attack against Anglo-Dutch forces in [Indonesia](/Indonesia). &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 20**: [Mongolians](/Mongolia) vote in favor of independence from China. &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 21**: [Women's suffrage](/Women%27s_suffrage): Women are granted the right to vote in the [French Legislative Election](/1945_French_legislative_election) for the first time.
*   **October 22**: [Rómulo Betancourt](/R%C3%B3mulo_Betancourt) is appointed provisional president of [Venezuela](/Venezuela). &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 24**:
    *   The [United Nations](/United_Nations) is officially founded through the ratification of [its Charter](/United_Nations_Charter) by [29 nations](/Enlargement_of_the_United_Nations). &#91;57&#93;
    *   The [International Court of Justice](/International_Court_of_Justice) ("World Court") is established under the framework of the [United Nations Charter](/United_Nations_Charter).
    *   Norwegian Nazi leader [Vidkun Quisling](/Vidkun_Quisling) is [executed by firing squad](/Execution_by_firing_squad) for committing [treason](/Treason) against Norway. &#91;57&#93;
*   **October 25**:
    *   WWII: Japanese armed forces in [Taiwan](/Taiwan) surrender to the Allies.
    *   [Getúlio Vargas](/Get%C3%BAlio_Vargas) is deposed as president in Brazil; [José Linhares](/Jos%C3%A9_Linhares) is appointed temporary president. &#91;57&#93;
    *   The [Osijek prison massacre](/Osijek_prison_massacre) is carried out by the Yugoslav secret police.
*   **October 27–November 20**: [Indonesian National Revolution](/Indonesian_National_Revolution): The [Battle of Surabaya](/Battle_of_Surabaya) takes place, where pro-independence [Indonesian](/Indonesia) soldiers and militia engage British and British Indian troops in [Surabaya](/Surabaya).
*   **October 29**:
    *   [Getúlio Vargas](/Get%C3%BAlio_Vargas) resigns from the presidency of Brazil.
    *   At [Gimbels](/Gimbels) Department Store in New York City, the first [ballpoint pens](/Ballpoint_pen) go on sale, priced at $12.50 each.
*   **October 30**: The undivided country of [India](/British_India) joins the [United Nations](/United_Nations).

#### November

*   Main article: [November 1945](/November_1945)

*   **November 1**:
    *   The new constitution of the [International Labour Organization](/International_Labour_Organization) comes into effect.
    *   [Telechron](/Telechron) introduces the model 8H59 Musalarm, recognized as the first [clock radio](/Clock_radio).
*   **November 5**: [Colombia](/Colombia) becomes a member of the [United Nations](/United_Nations).
*   **November 6**: [Indonesians](/Indonesia) reject an offer of autonomy proposed by the [Dutch](/Netherlands). &#91;57&#93;
*   **November 9**: [Soo Bahk Do](/Soo_Bahk_Do) and [Moo Duk Kwan](/Moo_Duk_Kwan) martial arts are established in [Korea](/Korea).
*   **November 10**: [Indonesian National Revolution](/Indonesian_National_Revolution): Following the killing of British officer Brigadier [A. W. S. Mallaby](/Aubertin_Walter_Sothern_Mallaby) on October 30, the [British Indian Army](/British_Indian_Army), in support of its allied Dutch colonial administration, commences an advance on [Surabaya](/Surabaya) in the [Dutch East Indies](/Dutch_East_Indies) against [Indonesian](/Indonesia) nationalists. Although the majority of the city is retaken within three days of intense fighting, the significant strength of the resistance leads to the commemoration of this day as [Heroes' Day](/Heroes%27_Day) (Hari Pahlawan) in Indonesia.
*   **November 11**: [1945 Yugoslavian parliamentary election](/1945_Yugoslavian_parliamentary_election): Marshal [Josip Broz Tito](/Josip_Broz_Tito) and the [People's Front](/People%27s_Front_(Yugoslavia)) secure a decisive majority (90%) in the Yugoslavian Assembly. &#91;57&#93;
*   **November 15**:
    *   [Harry S. Truman](/Harry_S._Truman), [Clement Attlee](/Clement_Attlee), and [Mackenzie King](/William_Lyon_Mackenzie_King) share information regarding nuclear technology with the U.N. and call for the establishment of a [United Nations Atomic Energy Commission](/United_Nations_Atomic_Energy_Commission). &#91;49&#93; &#91;57&#93;
    *   An offensive is launched in [Manchuria](/Manchuria) by the [Kuomintang](/Kuomintang) (Chinese Nationalists) to counter further infiltration by the [Chinese Communist Party](/Chinese_Communist_Party). &#91;57&#93;
*   **November 16**:
    *   [Charles de Gaulle](/Charles_de_Gaulle) is unanimously elected [president of France](/President_of_France) by the [provisional government](/Provisional_Government_of_the_French_Republic). &#91;57&#93;
    *   The United States controversially imports 88 German scientists to assist in the development of [rocket](/Rocket) technology.
    *   The foundation of [UNESCO](/UNESCO) (United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization) is agreed upon during a meeting in London.
*   **November 18**: The [Tudeh Party](/Tudeh_Party_of_Iran) initiates a bloodless coup, leading to the formation of [Azerbaijan](/Azerbaijan_People%27s_Government) within days. Soviet troops prevent [Iranian](/Iran) military intervention.
*   **November 20**: The [Nuremberg trials](/Nuremberg_trials) commence. Trials against 22 [Nazis](/Nazi) accused of [war crimes of World War II](/List_of_war_crimes) begin at the [Palace of Justice, Nuremberg](/Palace_of_Justice,_Nuremberg). &#91;57&#93;
*   **November 26**: U.S. ambassador to China [Patrick J. Hurley](/Patrick_J._Hurley) resigns after failing to broker an agreement between [Chiang Kai-shek](/Chiang_Kai-shek) and [Mao Tse-tung](/Mao_Tse-tung). &#91;57&#93;
*   **November 28**:
    *   The [1945 Balochistan earthquake](/1945_Balochistan_earthquake) triggers a tsunami and results in 4,000 fatalities.
    *   British [fascist](/Fascist) [John Amery](/John_Amery) pleads guilty to treason and is condemned to death. &#91;61&#93;
*   **November 29**:
    *   The [Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia](/Socialist_Federal_Republic_of_Yugoslavia) is declared (this day is celebrated as Republic Day until the 1990s). [Marshal Tito](/Josip_Broz_Tito) is appointed president.
    *   The assembly of the world's first general-purpose electronic computer, the Electronic Numerical Integrator Analyzer and Computer ([ENIAC](/ENIAC)), is completed in the United States. Occupying 1,800 square feet (170 m²) of floor space, it runs its first set of calculations.
*   **November 30**:
    *   The [Balochistan earthquake of 1945](/1945_Balochistan_earthquake) causes a tsunami and kills 4,000 people.
    *   British [fascist](/Fascist) [John Amery](/John_Amery) pleads guilty to treason and is condemned to death. &#91;61&#93;

#### December

*   Main article: [December 1945](/December_1945)

*   **December 2**:
    *   General [Eurico Gaspar Dutra](/Eurico_Gaspar_Dutra) is elected president of Brazil.
    *   French banks, including the [Bank of France](/Bank_of_France), [BNCI](/BNP_Paribas), [CNEP](/BNP_Paribas), [Crédit Lyonnais](/Cr%C3%A9dit_Lyonnais), and [Société Générale](/Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9_G%C3%A9n%C3%A9rale), are nationalized.
*   **December 3**: [Communist](/Communism) demonstrations in [Athens](/Athens) foreshadow the outbreak of the [Greek Civil War](/Greek_Civil_War).
*   **December 4**: The [United States Senate](/United_States_Senate) approves the entry of the United States into the [United Nations](/United_Nations) by a vote of 65 to 7.
*   **December 5**: [Flight 19](/Flight_19), consisting of five [United States Navy](/United_States_Navy) [Grumman TBF Avenger](/Grumman_TBF_Avenger) [torpedo bombers](/Torpedo_bomber), disappears during a training exercise originating from [Naval Air Station Fort Lauderdale](/Naval_Air_Station_Fort_Lauderdale).
*   **December 9**: American General [George S. Patton](/George_S._Patton) is involved in a vehicular accident in Germany, which leads to his death on December 21.
*   **December 27**: Twenty-one nations ratify the articles establishing the [World Bank](/World_Bank). &#91;62&#93;

### Date Unknown

*   A team at [Oak Ridge National Laboratory](/Oak_Ridge_National_Laboratory), under the leadership of [Charles D. Coryell](/Charles_D._Coryell), discovers the [chemical element](/Chemical_element) 61. This element is the only one remaining undiscovered between atomic numbers 1 and 96 on the [periodic table](/Periodic_table), and it is subsequently named [promethium](/Promethium). &#91;63&#93; Its discovery is attributed to the analysis of fission products from irradiated uranium fuel, though the announcement of its discovery is delayed until 1947.
*   The Australian government introduces an Assisted Passage Migration Scheme, designed to encourage the immigration of British subjects. The subsidized fare of £10 leads to these immigrants becoming known as "[Ten Pound Poms](/Ten_Pound_Poms)". &#91;64&#93;
*   The first instance of geothermal milk pasteurization is performed in [Klamath Falls, Oregon](/Klamath_Falls,_Oregon), United States.

